# UI Copy & Voice

All user-visible text must read like it was written by **an Indonesian ops/CS team lead**, not an AI or English marketing page translated overnight.

**Punctuation:** never use em dash (`—`). Use hyphen `-` or rephrase - see `writing-punctuation.mdc`.

## Voice

- **Direct, calm, operational** - the user is a busy CS agent or shop owner.
- **Short labels** - scannable in 1-2 seconds. No paragraphs in buttons or KPI titles.
- **Consistent terms** - reuse words already in the app (Customer, Percakapan, CS, Supervisor, Owner, Export, Audit Log).
- **Indonesian first** - natural spoken-office tone, not stiff textbook or literal Google Translate.

## Do (match existing app)

| Context | Good examples from this project |
|---------|----------------------------------|
| Buttons | Simpan, Batal, Hapus, Masuk, Buka Chat, Follow Up |
| Toasts | `Profil diperbarui`, `Pesan terkirim`, `Akses dibagikan` |
| Empty state | `Tidak ada customer dalam segment ini.` |
| Locked access | `Bagian ini khusus Supervisor & Owner` |
| Placeholders | `Cari nama, no HP...`, `Tulis template...`, `Alasan penolakan (wajib)` |
| Confirm | `Hapus akun agent ${name}?` - plain question, no drama |

## Do not (AI tells - never use)

- Marketing fluff: *mempermudah*, *solusi terpadu*, *transformasi digital*, *cutting-edge*, *powerful*, *seamless*, *leverage*, *empower*
- Over-celebration: *Berhasil!*, *Sukses!*, *Hebat!*, *Selamat, Anda telah...* (except login: `Selamat datang, ${name}!` - already established)
- Robotic success: *Operasi berhasil dilakukan*, *Data telah berhasil disimpan*
- Generic empty: *Tidak ada data*, *No results found*, *Belum ada apapun*
- Tutorial voice in UI: *Klik di sini untuk...*, *Silakan masukkan...*, *Pastikan Anda...*
- English in Indonesian screens: *Submit*, *Save changes*, *Learn more*, *Get started* (chat filter tabs Mine/Open are the documented exception)
- Emoji spam in labels - segment badges and filters use `SegmentIcon` (`lucide-react` via `@/lib/segment-icons`), not emoji or colored dots; don't add emoji to buttons, headings, card titles, or toasts
- Decorative emoji in UI chrome (🚨 👋 💰 etc.) - use `lucide-react` icons or plain text instead
- Title Case Every Word - use sentence case for descriptions: `Ringkasan customer & percakapan yang ditugaskan untukmu.`

## Label rules

- **Buttons:** verb only or verb + object - `Customer Baru`, not `Tambah Customer Baru Sekarang`
- **Section titles:** noun phrase - `Manajemen Agent`, `Template Balasan`
- **Subtitles:** one line, grey (`text-slate-500`) - explain scope, not features
- **Table headers:** short - `Nama`, `No HP`, `Terakhir Order` (not `Nama Lengkap Customer`)
- **Errors:** say what happened + what to do - `Alasan penolakan wajib diisi`, not `Validasi gagal`
- **Demo/disclaimer:** honest and brief - `Demo mode - pilih role untuk melihat perbedaan akses.`

## Before adding new copy

1. Search the repo for similar strings (`grep` toast messages, button labels).
2. Copy the **length and tone** of the closest existing screen.
3. Read aloud - if it sounds like a chatbot or landing page, rewrite shorter.

## Code vs UI

- **UI strings:** Indonesian (this rule).
- **Code, types, comments, commit messages:** English.
